race.comment: The $160,000 Listed Just Now. MIDNIGHT IN TOKYO (2) just ran into one better in the Keith Noud when resuming before getting the job done in the Tatts Classic last time out. Has placed four from six around this circuit and winning hoop Maloney retains the ride. Should measure up. Former NSW galloper LONHRO'S QUEEN (6) has been very competitive in all three runs since joining the new stable and is one from one at this track. Has to be included. ZASZOU (1) strips fitter third-up from the spell and must be respected out of the Maher camp. Top-three commodity. JUNQUEIRA (10) is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and can improve sharply without surprising. The well-related SUNSET DREAMING (15) (half to G1 winner Benedetta) best of the rest.
